observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipality of Mallig adopt a system of payroll payment through the Automated Teller Machine (ATMs) of banks which would result in:
Convenience on the part of the Management since payroll payments are distributed from the payroll account maintained in an authorized government depository bank to the individual accounts of the employees;
Convenience on the part of the employees since payrolls can be withdrawn anytime from ATM during their free time;
Decreases if not eliminates the risk of loss or misapplication of funds;
Reduces cash advances handled by the Disbursing Officer; and
On time liquidation of cash advances.

Thus, were recommended that the Municipal Accountant, General Services Officer, and Inventory Committee to:
Observe the proper conduct of physical count to come up with a reliable reports pursuant to the above cited COA Circular;
Prepare and submit the Report of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment on or before January 31 of the succeeding year;
Prepare and maintain Property Cards for all the agency properties and reconcile with the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards of the Accounting Office;
Thru the Disposal Committee to undertake the disposal proceedings and derecognize unserviceable properties from the accounting books and property records upon disposal thereof based on the approved Inventory and Inspection Report on Unserviceable Property (IIRUP); and
Pursue the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to finally establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the following department heads/committee for the compliance with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015:
Municipal Engineer;
Provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects as per Item VII.c.1 of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015.
Municipal Accountant;
Submit the required copies of PPE Local Road Network Ledger Cards (Annex D format) per Item VII a.1 of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015;
Update the yearly required disclosures as needed;
Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and
Prepare a lapsing schedule regularly for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year; and
Municipal General Services Officer.
Maintain and submit Local Road Inventory and Road Maps; and
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all roads and its components and submit the same to the Audit Team (Annex E format) per Item VII b.2 of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015.
We also recommended that the Inventory Committee submit Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network System (RPCLRN) supported with Local Road Network Maps (Annex C format) per Item VI.3 of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015.

