We recommended that the Management observe the following measures:
The Municipal Accountant should ensure that all cash advances are liquidated immediately as soon as the purpose has been served, otherwise send a letter of demand to the concerned officers and employees. As for those who already retired or resigned from the service, make a final demand for its settlement and in case of failure to settle, submit the entire records to the Municipal Legal Office for the institution of legal remedies;
Remind the Municipal Accountant that non-bonded officers and employees should not be granted any cash advances unless if it is for travelling purposes;
Refrain from processing the disbursement vouchers for a new cash advance for those with previous unsettled cash advances; and
Advise the concern officers and employees liquidate immediately the amount stated above to forestall the issuance of Notice of Disallowance.

We recommended that the Management observe the following measures:
Stop the practice of each Department/ Office procure their own Office Supplies/ Medicine Inventory;
Require the Municipal Treasure refrain from paying the reimbursement of the procured Office Supplies/Medicine Inventory unless the procurement was emergency in nature;
Require the GSO that at the beginning of the year, he shall prepare a PR for supplies and materials needed for the quarter based on the approved Annual Procurement Program. Subsequent requisition from stock shall be made by the head of office or department needing the supplies;
Require the Municipal Accountant maintain a Supplies Ledger Card (SLC) for each type of supplies; and
Require the GSO or the property custodian maintain a Stock Card (SC) for each type of supplies.

We recommended that the;
General Services Officer conduct physical count of all inventories, prepare the corresponding Report on the Physical Count of Inventories, and submit the same to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the reported balances in the books and to the Office of the Auditor.
Municipal Accountant record the inventory following the Perpetual Inventory Method.
